    {
      "paragraph_name": "PAUTBPCB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This copybook defines the data structure PAUTBPCB, which is likely used to hold information related to an IMS Program Communication Block (PCB). The structure includes fields such as PAUT-DBDNAME (database name), PAUT-SEG-LEVEL (segment level), PAUT-PCB-STATUS (PCB status), PAUT-PCB-PROCOPT (processing options), PAUT-SEG-NAME (segment name), PAUT-KEYFB-NAME (key feedback length), PAUT-NUM-SENSEGS (number of sensitive segments), and PAUT-KEYFB (key feedback area). The PAUT-KEYFB field is defined as PIC X(255), suggesting it's designed to hold a variable-length key feedback string. The copybook does not perform any processing logic itself; it simply defines the data structure for use by other programs. The intended use is for programs interacting with an IMS database to access PCB information.",
